  "text": "Refresh 2024-11-26T17:57:58.952ZThat brings to an end our coverage of the best Black Friday Ninja deals you can buy today. But don't worry, we'll be back tomorrow to update you on all the best prices and let you know if anything has had an even better discount applied. 2024-11-26T17:03:08.759Z(Image credit: Future)The Ninja Creami isn't at the cheapest price I've ever seen it right now, but if your heart is set on buying it, there are still discounts available at various retailers. Its lowest price is at John Lewis for £149 for the standard colourway, or you can pick it up in copper on Amazon for even less.It's by far my favourite Ninja appliance to use at home. If you also love tucking into a sweet treat of an evening, you'll love this one too.Ninja Creami | £199.99, now £141.99 at Amazon 2024-11-26T16:19:31.691Z(Image credit: Future)It's that time of day when I'm thinking about what I'm going to have for my dinner, which brings me nicely to one of my favourite winter warmer Ninja deals: the Ninja PossibleCooker.Dubbed in our review as much more useful than a normal slow cooker, the PossibleCooker is now at its cheapest price over on Amazon. For an appliance that can help you cook all of your favourite hearty meals (and your Christmas dinner), look no further.Ninja PossibleCooker 8-in-1 Slow Cooker | £149.99, now £109.00 at Amazon 2024-11-26T15:23:37.920Z(Image credit: Future/Ninja)If you have a Ninja fan in your life who is already kitted out with all of the appliances they need, then this smart thermometer could be the perfect Christmas gift. It's heat-safe up to 370°C and waterproof too, for all your BBQing needs.Ninja ProChef Wireless Thermometer WP100EU | £89.99, now £69.99 at Ninja 2024-11-26T14:20:30.536Z(Image credit: Future)If you too would love to make perfect pancakes like our expert reviewer Helen McCue did, then listen up.The Ninja Sizzle, which is an indoor grill and flat plate, is perfect for breakfasts and dinners. Helen used it to cook up a storm with a range of foods, saying it was great for griddle style cooking in her Ninja Sizzle review. It's now massively reduced too!Ninja Sizzle | £214.99, now £109.99 at John Lewis 2024-11-26T13:43:36.280Z(Image credit: Future/Ninja)Ninja's cookware has consistently impressed me during my tests, and now its most versatile pan is on sale.The PossiblePan is designed to be functional enough for any cooking task, with an integrated strainer and an included spatula. This one is already sold out on Ninja's website, so act fast via John Lewis if you like the look of this one.Ninja ZEROSTICK Non-Stick 9-in-1 PossiblePan | £129.99, now £79.99 at John Lewis 2024-11-26T12:34:12.448Z(Image credit: Future/Ninja)If all of the Ninja jargon leaves you feeling confused, then I've got just the read for you.Our piece on which Ninja Foodi you should buy and why has an extensive breakdown of all of the benefits of owning an appliance from the brand. You'll be confident about ditching your oven for good for a Ninja once you've read it. 2024-11-26T12:08:18.663Z(Image credit: Future/Ninja)The Ninja knife blocks are a hidden gem when it comes to value for money. For the price you'll pay, you get 5 quality knives plus an integrated sharpener.That means that you could be set for life (or at least the next 10 years) when it comes to kitchen knives with just one purchase.Ninja Foodi StaySharp Knife Block (5 Piece Set) | £169.99, now £109.99 at Amazon 2024-11-26T11:12:57.520Z(Image credit: Future)Unless you're a hardcore Ninja fan, you probably haven't heard of the Combi but it might just be the most versatile product from the brand out there. It won 4.5 stars from our expert tester in our Ninja Combi review and has 12 functions in total.That means you'll pay less than £20 per function at its new sale price, which sounds like a fantastic deal to me!Ninja Combi | was £280, now £229.99 at Ninja 2024-11-26T10:42:57.717Z(Image credit: Future/Ninja)What about the Ninja Slushi, I hear you ask? Sold out via Ninja, the Slushi is the hype kitchen appliance of this year.Luckily, I've found the one place it's in stock: on Amazon, though you will pay an extra £76.72 in shipping fees on top of the RRP if you go down this route. But if you just can't wait to make slushies at home, this is your best bet.Ninja Slushi | £376.72 at Amazon 2024-11-26T10:07:29.810Z(Image credit: Future/Currys)Even though I'm an obvious air fryer convert, I'm the first person to agree that these appliances could be a lot prettier.That's why I'm a big fan of the Currys white Ninja air fryer range, which features the Dual Zone and the Double Stack. I roped in Ideal Home's Content Editor Holly Cockburn to weigh in with her opinion on picking up an air fryer in the white colourway.'Not only is this air fryer actually super chic,' says Holly, 'but it will also look far better alongside cream (or even pink) small appliances if black isn't your thing. I'm dreaming of it sitting atop a marble-effect worktop in a navy or light grey kitchen - it will complete the look.'Catch them on sale if you like the look too.NINJA Foodi MAX Dual Zone in White | £229.00, now £169.99 at CurrysNinja Double Stack XL 2 Drawer Air Fryer 9.5L | Was £269.99, now £219.00 at Currys 2024-11-26T09:38:09.333Z(Image credit: Future/Ninja)To kick off coverage of the price-checked best Ninja deals around, what better place to start than with my favourite deal of the season on our top-rated air fryer ever?To keep it brief, I'll summarise what is so great about this air fryer from our 5-star Ninja FlexDrawer review.1. It's actually big enough to replace your oven. Our reviewer cooked a 2kg leg of lamb in the MEGAZONE without issue. 2. It's got the versatility for family cooking. If you need to use 2 drawers to cater to different dinner preferences, you can just pop the divider in. 3. It's supremely powerful, and can cook oven chips in silly-quick time.Ninja Foodi FlexDrawer | £269.99, now £199.99 at Amazon 2024-11-26T09:19:49.409Z(Image credit: Future)Hello! I'm Molly and I'll be running you through Ideal Home's coverage of the best Black Friday Ninja deals. I'm Ideal Home's Kitchen Appliances Editor and Certified Expert for cooking gadgets and cookware.I've worked on every product release from Ninja in the past three years and I've tested all of the classics: the Ninja Dual Zone Air Fryer, the Ninja Creami Deluxe, the Ninja Speedi and even the brand's toaster and kettle.My favourite Ninja has to be the Creami Deluxe, which I love using to create all sorts of sweet treats at home but I spend a lot of my time in the world of the best Ninja air fryers too.",
